<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<p id="demo">Click the button to change the text in this paragraph.</p>

<button type="button" onclick="myfunction()">Try it</button>

<script>
function myfunction(){
    document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML="Hello World";

}
</script>

</body>
</html>
<!--
getElementById() method returns the element that has the ID attribute with the specified value
used to manipulate, get info from an element on your document
return null if no element with specified ID exists
return first element with the specified ID if more than one element exists with a given ID in the whole document
-->
